WEBVTT

00:01.620 --> 00:03.960
[ Sizzling ]

00:03.960 --> 00:05.880
Mom, you made
another lasagna?

00:05.880 --> 00:07.460
I'm just staying busy.

00:07.460 --> 00:09.420
Oh, because you've been
unemployed for three months

00:09.420 --> 00:10.710
and the kids are gone
all day at school,

00:10.710 --> 00:11.880
so you're feeling
purposeless?

00:11.880 --> 00:14.170
Where the hell
are you getting that?

00:14.170 --> 00:16.290
Ladies' Home Journal.

00:16.290 --> 00:18.250
I was killing time waiting
for my dentist appointment.

00:18.250 --> 00:20.290
Ooh, also, I learned
how to make a "she shed."

00:21.620 --> 00:23.380
We need to do something
about my clothes.

00:23.380 --> 00:25.080
See?

00:25.080 --> 00:26.620
I have a purpose.

00:26.620 --> 00:27.960
What do you need, honey?

00:27.960 --> 00:29.210
Now that
I'm out of special ed,

00:29.210 --> 00:30.960
I have to start dressing
like someone

00:30.960 --> 00:33.040
who doesn't have her mittens
sewn into her jacket.

00:33.040 --> 00:34.960
Mommy stands
ready to help.

00:34.960 --> 00:37.210
Actually,
I don't need your help.

00:37.210 --> 00:39.250
In fact,
you're part of the problem.

00:39.250 --> 00:42.460
Every piece of clothing I own
has fruit on it.

00:42.460 --> 00:44.460
This skirt is covered
in bananas.

00:44.460 --> 00:46.120
Tell me --
what were you thinking?

00:46.120 --> 00:47.330
Well,
maybe she was just --

00:47.330 --> 00:48.830
Don't defend her.

00:48.830 --> 00:50.620
I want Taylor to take me.

00:50.620 --> 00:52.080
Fine.

00:52.080 --> 00:54.040
Taylor, take Anna-Kat
shopping tomorrow.

00:54.040 --> 00:55.420
I've got things going on!

00:55.420 --> 00:57.040
Unlike you,
I have a life.

00:57.040 --> 01:00.710
Learning to take responsibility
is also on your list of things

01:00.710 --> 01:03.170
you need to accomplish
before you go to college.

01:03.170 --> 01:05.000
Come on,
there's so many other ways

01:05.000 --> 01:06.250
I could take
responsibility.

01:06.250 --> 01:07.540
Such as?

01:09.250 --> 01:11.290
I was hoping there wasn't
gonna be a follow-up.

01:11.290 --> 01:13.250
I mean, what if she only wants
to dress like Eleven

01:13.250 --> 01:14.580
from "Stranger Things"?

01:14.580 --> 01:16.250
And not
cute, season 3 Eleven.

01:16.250 --> 01:18.170
Dirty pink dress,
season 1 Eleven.

01:18.170 --> 01:20.290
Just use
your best judgment.

01:20.290 --> 01:22.620
Best judgment?
Do I have that?

01:22.620 --> 01:24.540
Greg: Katie?
In the kitchen!

01:24.540 --> 01:26.540
What?!
I thought we discussed

01:26.540 --> 01:28.620
we weren't gonna
have conversations
in different rooms!

01:28.620 --> 01:30.540
What?!
I'm coming!

01:30.540 --> 01:32.210
This is
90% of marriage.

01:32.210 --> 01:34.460
What's
the other 10%?

01:34.460 --> 01:37.080
Wondering what life would
be like if we didn't have...

01:38.290 --> 01:39.500
...pets.

01:39.500 --> 01:43.960
♪♪

01:43.960 --> 01:46.380
Despite the nonstop
tenement-style hollering

01:46.380 --> 01:48.880
in this house, I finished
my Teen Help Line application.

01:48.880 --> 01:50.040
That's great, honey!

01:50.040 --> 01:51.830
Next step,
rock this interview.

01:51.830 --> 01:54.210
I think you could really benefit
by helping those in need.

01:54.210 --> 01:55.960
[ Scoffs ]
I know I can benefit.

01:55.960 --> 01:58.750
This is exactly
the sappy, humanitarian garbage

01:58.750 --> 01:59.710
Harvard is looking for.

01:59.710 --> 02:01.420
Greg: Katie!

02:01.420 --> 02:03.670
I'm gonna go drop this off at
the Teen Help Line offices now.

02:03.670 --> 02:05.080
Good luck.

02:05.080 --> 02:06.080
You too.

02:06.080 --> 02:07.250
With what?

02:07.250 --> 02:08.620
[ Scoffs ]

02:08.620 --> 02:10.540
The fact that you don't know
makes me even sadder.

02:10.540 --> 02:12.330
Oh.

02:12.330 --> 02:13.920
What?!

02:13.920 --> 02:15.250
Why are you calling me?

02:15.250 --> 02:16.790
Is there another moth?

02:16.790 --> 02:19.380
Crazy news. I just
got off the phone with Stan.

02:19.380 --> 02:20.830
He and Chloe
are back together.

02:20.830 --> 02:22.460
How is that possible?

02:22.460 --> 02:25.420
Stan left Chloe and married
that woman half his age.

02:25.420 --> 02:26.540
Chloe hates him.

02:26.540 --> 02:27.620
"Hated."

02:27.620 --> 02:30.040
On his honeymoon,
Stan had a stroke.

02:30.040 --> 02:32.040
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my God!

02:32.040 --> 02:33.330
He's okay,
but his new wife

02:33.330 --> 02:35.380
annulled the marriage
and left him.

02:35.380 --> 02:36.750
I was thinking of inviting
some of the guys

02:36.750 --> 02:38.380
from the Historical Guild over
to welcome him home.

02:38.380 --> 02:40.210
Ugh. Do you know
what that means?

02:40.210 --> 02:41.880
Now that Stan is
back in your life,

02:41.880 --> 02:43.250
Chloe is back in mine.

02:43.250 --> 02:44.580
Honey,
if you would just --

02:44.580 --> 02:45.620
If I would just what?

02:48.670 --> 02:50.000
Let's end it here.
I don't feel safe.

02:50.000 --> 02:53.000
♪♪

02:58.790 --> 03:01.710
There are a lot of jobs
out there for women your age.

03:01.710 --> 03:04.290
The dean's wife started selling
this organic makeup line.

03:04.290 --> 03:05.460
She has this cool trunk,

03:05.460 --> 03:07.500
and she takes it
to her friends' houses,

03:07.500 --> 03:10.580
and they drink wine
and put their faces on together.

03:11.960 --> 03:13.460
How stupid is that?

03:14.830 --> 03:16.210
I have every faith
you're gonna find something

03:16.210 --> 03:17.210
that's perfect for you.

03:17.210 --> 03:18.620
Thank you.

03:18.620 --> 03:20.670
So, what's the plan
for tonight?

03:20.670 --> 03:21.670
Oh, glad you asked.

03:21.670 --> 03:23.460
When a wounded soldier
returns home,

03:23.460 --> 03:25.330
we celebrate him
with a meal and a song.

03:25.330 --> 03:26.960
♪ Come join -- ♪
Heard enough.

03:26.960 --> 03:28.500
[ Door opens, closes ]

03:28.500 --> 03:30.210
Hey, Oliver.
Is everything okay?

03:30.210 --> 03:31.880
No, everything is
not okay.

03:31.880 --> 03:34.330
When I dropped off
my Teen Help Line application,

03:34.330 --> 03:36.040
I talked with
all these other kids

03:36.040 --> 03:37.580
who are a lock
to get accepted.

03:37.580 --> 03:40.750
One was an orphan,
one was a refugee,

03:40.750 --> 03:43.210
one had just come from donating
a kidney to a complete stranger.

03:43.210 --> 03:45.210
Just to screw
with your life.

03:45.210 --> 03:46.210
I know!

03:46.210 --> 03:47.670
There's no way
I'm getting in.

03:47.670 --> 03:49.580
I haven't suffered enough.

03:49.580 --> 03:51.040
I mean [Scoffs]

03:51.040 --> 03:53.380
I suffer...

03:53.380 --> 03:55.380
but this isn't
the kind of suffering

03:55.380 --> 03:57.330
that impresses
professional do-gooders.

03:57.330 --> 03:58.830
I don't have an angle.

03:58.830 --> 03:59.880
I wouldn't worry about it.

03:59.880 --> 04:01.170
If you don't
get into this program,

04:01.170 --> 04:02.460
you'll find something else
that'll make you stand out.

04:02.460 --> 04:05.580
Dad, Teen Help Line is
incredibly prestigious.

04:05.580 --> 04:08.290
If I don't get in,
I can kiss Harvard goodbye.

04:08.290 --> 04:10.790
Can we do 23andMe?
Find out I'm Inuit?

04:10.790 --> 04:12.040
Navajo?

04:12.040 --> 04:13.580
I won't do
genetic testing.

04:13.580 --> 04:15.620
I don't want
the relatives I have now.

04:15.620 --> 04:17.500
Why would I go
digging up more?

04:17.500 --> 04:18.920
[ Patriotic music plays ]

04:18.920 --> 04:21.000
Greg: Be always at war
with your vices

04:21.000 --> 04:22.380
and at peace
with your neighbors.

04:22.380 --> 04:23.620
Together: Hear! Hear!

04:25.750 --> 04:26.790
We're here.

04:27.670 --> 04:28.790
Hey, Stan!

04:28.790 --> 04:30.080
Both: Look who's back!

04:30.080 --> 04:31.620
Jinx!
You owe me a mead!

04:31.620 --> 04:33.330
[ Both laugh ]

04:33.330 --> 04:35.170
Good to see you, buddy.
Come on in.

04:35.170 --> 04:37.330
Katie.
Chloe.

04:37.330 --> 04:40.790
I have to say, I was surprised
to hear that you took Stan back.

04:40.790 --> 04:42.170
It was very big of you.

04:42.170 --> 04:44.120
Listen,
just because last year,

04:44.120 --> 04:46.670
we had one fleeting moment
of not hating each other

04:46.670 --> 04:48.380
doesn't mean
we're throwing on the jammies

04:48.380 --> 04:49.920
and braiding
each other's hair.

04:49.920 --> 04:52.380
I mean, with
our wildly different sizes,

04:52.380 --> 04:54.710
we could make
a great comedy duo, but friends?

04:54.710 --> 04:56.040
Get real.

04:56.040 --> 04:57.380
[ Sighs ]
So relieved.

04:57.380 --> 05:00.000
Hating you is
the greatest joy of my life.

05:00.000 --> 05:01.500
Besides my kids.
Yeah.

05:01.500 --> 05:03.790
Actually, it goes Anna-Kat,
Taylor, hating you, Oliver.

05:03.790 --> 05:05.500
Mm-hmm.

05:05.500 --> 05:07.460
But I'm telling you,
waterfall ice climbing

05:07.460 --> 05:09.290
has nothing on para-hawking.

05:09.290 --> 05:11.080
The rush you get
flying next to raptors --

05:11.080 --> 05:12.710
ooh, it is
quite exhilarating.

05:12.710 --> 05:13.960
Let me tell you, sir.

05:13.960 --> 05:15.540
[ Chuckles ] Is it?

05:15.540 --> 05:17.790
But, of course, now I'm on
my greatest adventure of all --

05:17.790 --> 05:19.330
being back
with my darling Chloe.

05:19.330 --> 05:20.420
Ohh.
Mm.

05:20.420 --> 05:21.920
That's enough.

05:21.920 --> 05:24.120
Game night,
huh, gentlemen?

05:24.120 --> 05:25.670
Yeah, we're playing
Truth or Dare,

05:25.670 --> 05:27.420
George Washington-style --
all truths.

05:27.420 --> 05:28.880
Oh.

05:28.880 --> 05:31.250
Well, you better watch this guy,
'cause he loves to cheat!

05:31.250 --> 05:33.250
[ Laughter ]
One truth for Chloe!

05:33.250 --> 05:35.000
No more ale for you,
Ross!

05:35.000 --> 05:36.960
Katie:
Here it is, boys.

05:36.960 --> 05:39.330
The lasagna
Paul Revere served

05:39.330 --> 05:41.710
at the Battle of
You Guys Are Nerds.

05:41.710 --> 05:43.620
Lasagna?

05:43.620 --> 05:45.250
Mm. Not surprised.

05:45.250 --> 05:46.880
It's the sweatpants
of food.

05:46.880 --> 05:48.920
And you are
the adult underpants of people.

05:48.920 --> 05:49.920
Ooh, good one.

05:49.920 --> 05:51.500
Hey,
I heard you were fired.

05:51.500 --> 05:52.670
Figures.

05:52.670 --> 05:54.290
Not everybody
can run a company

05:54.290 --> 05:56.210
and manage a family,
like I do.

05:56.210 --> 05:58.330
I wasn't fired.
I quit.

05:58.330 --> 05:59.670
Po-tay-to, po-tah-to.

05:59.670 --> 06:01.750
Neither of which I eat --
obviously.

06:01.750 --> 06:03.790
You know,
the sad thing for you is,

06:03.790 --> 06:07.080
you're too poor to even enjoy
all the free time you have now.

06:07.080 --> 06:09.210
I mean, what on Earth
are you doing with yourself?

06:09.210 --> 06:13.620
I am exploring
many, many avenues.

06:13.620 --> 06:15.000
[ Laughs ]

06:15.000 --> 06:17.040
That's code
for "I have nothing."

06:17.040 --> 06:20.080
No purpose, no options,
no water feature in your yard.

06:20.080 --> 06:21.080
Sad.

06:21.080 --> 06:22.710
You don't know anything.

06:22.710 --> 06:24.710
Katie:
She knows everything!

06:24.710 --> 06:27.120
I have no plan, no purpose,
and no koi pond.

06:27.120 --> 06:28.830
Quick, change the subject.

06:28.830 --> 06:31.290
The "Cats" movie
looks insane, right?

06:31.290 --> 06:33.710
I know, but, like,
kind of sexy. Huh?

06:33.710 --> 06:36.120
I mean, maybe it's just me,
but rrrr!

06:36.120 --> 06:37.790
Ew! Gross!
It is just you.

06:38.960 --> 06:41.120
Nice job, Katie!
You're back on top.

06:44.330 --> 06:47.210
Even Chloe Brown Mueller
figured it out.

06:47.210 --> 06:50.040
I'm turning 40 soon.
I'm adrift.

06:50.040 --> 06:52.080
I have no direction
in life.

06:52.080 --> 06:53.790
You're a mom.
It's not like you do nothing.

06:53.790 --> 06:55.460
I'm a mom.
I do nothing.

06:55.460 --> 06:58.170
I can't use my kids
as an excuse anymore.

06:58.170 --> 07:00.380
Anna-Kat wants Taylor
to help her with everything,

07:00.380 --> 07:02.750
and Oliver is ironing
his own shirts

07:02.750 --> 07:05.120
because I don't go slowly enough
around the buttons.

07:05.120 --> 07:07.330
[ Chuckles ]
They're putting me
out of a job!

07:07.330 --> 07:09.210
You just have to find something
that's right for you.

07:09.210 --> 07:12.420
Or, hear me out, you could put
this whole problem behind you

07:12.420 --> 07:14.710
for nine more years
by having another baby.

07:17.040 --> 07:18.880
[ Laughter ]

07:21.830 --> 07:23.880
Oh, I needed that.

07:23.880 --> 07:25.670
Greg suggests
that I start selling

07:25.670 --> 07:28.170
that organic makeup
that comes in the big trunk.

07:28.170 --> 07:30.540
You are never
Yeah, never.
doing that.

07:30.540 --> 07:32.040
Isn't Suzanne Sutton
a career counselor now?

07:32.040 --> 07:33.250
You should go
talk to her.

07:33.250 --> 07:36.040
Oh!
Is Suzanne your type?

07:36.040 --> 07:37.080
Knock it off, Doris.

07:37.080 --> 07:38.540
What is going on
with you two?

07:38.540 --> 07:40.790
Well, apparently,
I don't "do it" for Angela.

07:40.790 --> 07:41.830
I didn't say that.

07:41.830 --> 07:43.330
I said
I think you're attractive.

07:43.330 --> 07:44.960
I'm just not
attracted to you.

07:44.960 --> 07:46.250
I think you are.

07:46.250 --> 07:48.380
If you weren't, you wouldn't be
so defensive about it.

07:48.380 --> 07:49.670
Look at this.
Hmm.

07:49.670 --> 07:53.170
[ Moaning ]

07:53.170 --> 07:56.120
Oopsie-daisy.
I got all dirty.

07:56.120 --> 07:57.330
Ahh!

07:57.330 --> 07:59.500
Hey, Katie.
I heard I could find you here.

07:59.500 --> 08:02.380
Doris, Angela,
you know Stan.

08:02.380 --> 08:03.710
Hey, Stan.

08:03.710 --> 08:05.420
Hey, buddy.
Gotta go.

08:07.580 --> 08:09.670
You know, ever since
the stroke, people react
in one of two ways --

08:09.670 --> 08:10.920
they either run away
or they just stare.

08:10.920 --> 08:11.960
Like this.

08:14.040 --> 08:15.580
I thought
I was a better person.

08:15.580 --> 08:17.880
Katie, may I speak to you
in private for one moment?

08:17.880 --> 08:20.120
Of course.

08:20.120 --> 08:22.920
Now, I hope I'm not imposing,
but I was wondering if you had

08:22.920 --> 08:25.500
any of that wonderful lasagna
left over from last night.

08:25.500 --> 08:27.790
Sure. I'll bring it
by your house.

08:27.790 --> 08:29.250
No. No, no, no.
I'll come to you.

08:29.250 --> 08:30.880
Chloe cannot find out
about this.

08:30.880 --> 08:32.880
If there's two things she hates
more than me right now,

08:32.880 --> 08:34.040
it's you and carbs.

08:34.040 --> 08:35.670
Thank you, Stan.

08:35.670 --> 08:38.500
I know she hates me, but it's
really nice to hear sometimes.

08:38.500 --> 08:39.670
I mean,
she really hates you.

08:39.670 --> 08:40.540
Mm-hmm. I know.

08:40.540 --> 08:42.540
♪♪

08:42.540 --> 08:45.500
We got fruit-free clothes,
a backpack,

08:45.500 --> 08:47.620
a new dangly thing
hanging off your backpack.

08:47.620 --> 08:49.080
If you were
in my fifth-grade class,

08:49.080 --> 08:50.210
I'd let you
sit next to me.

08:50.210 --> 08:51.920
Wait. There's something else
I need.

08:51.920 --> 08:53.790
Mom would never
sign off on that.

08:53.790 --> 08:55.080
Mom put you in charge.

08:55.080 --> 08:57.330
This is your chance
to think on your own.

08:57.330 --> 08:58.620
Am I old enough
to get my ears pierced?

08:59.710 --> 09:01.040
Yes.

09:01.040 --> 09:02.790
Yes, you are.
[ Chuckles ]

09:02.790 --> 09:03.830
[ Crash ]

09:04.790 --> 09:05.880
It wasn't me.

09:05.880 --> 09:08.080
♪♪

09:08.080 --> 09:11.210
My greatest achievement is
raising three fantastic kids.

09:12.460 --> 09:15.380
Also, in college, my alcohol
tolerance was very high.

09:15.380 --> 09:17.380
It's not anymore,
but it used to be.

09:17.380 --> 09:18.420
Type that in.

09:18.420 --> 09:20.210
Mm.

09:20.210 --> 09:22.290
And why did you leave
your last job?

09:22.290 --> 09:23.580
My boss was a [bleep]

09:23.580 --> 09:25.000
and my clients
were also [bleep].

09:27.250 --> 09:28.290
[ Chuckles nervously ]

09:28.290 --> 09:30.250
That word's not
in the drop-down menu,

09:30.250 --> 09:32.750
so we'll just click
"creative differences."

09:32.750 --> 09:37.080
♪♪

09:37.080 --> 09:39.380
Wait.
What if it hurts?

09:39.380 --> 09:41.420
What if they accidentally
give me those ear disks,

09:41.420 --> 09:43.080
like the guy
at the supermarket?

09:43.080 --> 09:44.750
Some days,
he forgets to put them in,

09:44.750 --> 09:46.540
and they're just
big, floppy holes.

09:46.540 --> 09:48.330
If you're really scared,
you don't have to do it.

09:48.330 --> 09:50.040
But all the other girls
in my new class

09:50.040 --> 09:51.750
have their ears pierced.

09:51.750 --> 09:53.540
Well, what if I go first and
show you it's not a big deal?

09:53.540 --> 09:54.750
You'd do that for me?

09:54.750 --> 09:56.620
Of course.
I owe you.

09:56.620 --> 09:58.670
You stopped me from trying
to pet that angry dog.

09:58.670 --> 09:59.710
Coyote.

09:59.710 --> 10:01.080
Whatever his name was,
he was mean.

10:04.670 --> 10:05.710
[ Computer chimes ]

10:05.710 --> 10:07.210
Well,
the results are in.

10:07.210 --> 10:09.580
So, as far
as a career goes,

10:09.580 --> 10:13.330
you would make an excellent
long-haul truck driver!

10:13.330 --> 10:15.710
Aah!
Congratulations!

10:15.710 --> 10:17.080
Truck driver?

10:17.080 --> 10:18.710
Well,
the algorithm determined

10:18.710 --> 10:20.710
that you shouldn't
manage people...

10:20.710 --> 10:23.250
or be managed by people...

10:23.250 --> 10:25.460
or interact with the public
in any way.

10:25.460 --> 10:27.040
So, what do we do now?

10:27.040 --> 10:30.750
Um, it says here
I'm supposed to call the police.

10:30.750 --> 10:34.790
♪♪

10:34.790 --> 10:36.710
[ Sighs ]

10:36.710 --> 10:38.250
Good news.

10:38.250 --> 10:40.380
I figured out what
can set me apart for
the interview tomorrow.

10:40.380 --> 10:42.330
I'm glad someone
has their life figured out,

10:42.330 --> 10:45.040
because I have never felt
more lost.

10:45.040 --> 10:46.960
I just came from
a career counselor --

10:46.960 --> 10:48.500
Let me just head this off.

10:48.500 --> 10:50.790
Parents don't come to their kids
with problems.

10:50.790 --> 10:52.540
We don't see you
as real people.

10:52.540 --> 10:53.710
Who needs a job

10:53.710 --> 10:56.040
when being a mother
is so rewarding?

10:56.040 --> 10:57.750
Uh-huh.
Back to me.

10:57.750 --> 11:01.120
It would help with my interview
if I came from a troubled home.

11:01.120 --> 11:04.250
Do you mind if I put you under
a 72-hour psychiatric hold?

11:04.250 --> 11:06.920
Yes, I mind!

11:06.920 --> 11:09.500
Oliver, you don't need
all these tricks.

11:09.500 --> 11:11.790
You are
a smart, driven kid,

11:11.790 --> 11:13.380
and I have no doubt

11:13.380 --> 11:15.420
that you're going to get in
on your own merits.

11:15.420 --> 11:17.080
Okay, Greg.

11:17.080 --> 11:20.120
♪♪

11:20.120 --> 11:22.540
Taylor, I just want to say,
you're my hero.

11:22.540 --> 11:23.880
Thank you!

11:23.880 --> 11:25.170
I mean, when Mom sees

11:25.170 --> 11:26.920
that you let me get my ears
pierced against her wishes,

11:26.920 --> 11:28.580
she's gonna go crazy

11:28.580 --> 11:30.580
and add another 500 things
to that list of yours.

11:30.580 --> 11:31.960
You think?

11:31.960 --> 11:33.250
[ Chuckles ]
Definitely.

11:33.250 --> 11:34.330
But you don't care.

11:34.330 --> 11:35.880
I don't?
No.

11:35.880 --> 11:37.710
And she's gonna
ground you forever.

11:37.710 --> 11:39.670
But I have that party I'm
going to with Trip on Saturday.

11:39.670 --> 11:40.460
Not anymore.

11:42.000 --> 11:44.040
Okay, new plan --
we're going to hide your ears.

11:44.040 --> 11:45.880
For how long?

11:45.880 --> 11:47.040
Until I go to college.

11:47.040 --> 11:48.580
That could easily
be never!

11:48.580 --> 11:53.380
♪♪

11:53.380 --> 11:55.460
[ Doorbell rings ]

11:55.460 --> 11:59.620
♪♪

11:59.620 --> 12:00.540
[ Chuckling ] Hey!

12:00.540 --> 12:01.830
Here you go.

12:01.830 --> 12:02.960
Thank you so much.

12:02.960 --> 12:04.960
And again, please don't
tell Chloe about this.

12:04.960 --> 12:07.040
Also, could you ask Greg
to get me a clean cup of urine?

12:08.080 --> 12:09.290
[ Whispering ]
She tests my sugar levels.

12:09.290 --> 12:11.170
Sure.
Thanks.

12:11.170 --> 12:13.580
Most people would be annoyed,

12:13.580 --> 12:16.750
but feeding Stan is actually
giving my life a purpose

12:16.750 --> 12:18.790
because it combines
two of my favorite things --

12:18.790 --> 12:19.880
cooking...

12:19.880 --> 12:21.710
Who's the best?
You are!

12:21.710 --> 12:24.080
...and messing with Chloe
behind her back.

12:24.080 --> 12:26.960
Oh, I feel a swagger walk
coming on.

12:26.960 --> 12:30.880
♪♪

12:30.880 --> 12:32.830
[ Car door closes ]

12:32.830 --> 12:35.080
I thought you were supposed to
get a cool-kid makeover.

12:35.080 --> 12:36.750
What's with the dumb hat?

12:36.750 --> 12:38.540
The lady who bought
the banana skirt

12:38.540 --> 12:40.580
should really stay out
of these conversations.

12:40.580 --> 12:42.920
[ Tapping ]

12:42.920 --> 12:44.210
Hey, you.

12:44.210 --> 12:45.620
Here you go.

12:45.620 --> 12:47.000
Thank you.

12:47.000 --> 12:48.710
Hopefully one day,
I'll be able to eat this

12:48.710 --> 12:50.420
when I'm not cowering
in the garage next
to the water heater.

12:50.420 --> 12:51.540
Ugh.

12:51.540 --> 12:53.000
♪♪

12:53.000 --> 12:54.290
[ Line ringing ]

12:54.290 --> 12:55.960
Stan! Why aren't you
picking up?!

12:55.960 --> 12:57.000
Ugh!

12:57.960 --> 12:59.290
[ Gasps ]

12:59.290 --> 13:00.500
Maria!

13:02.290 --> 13:04.250
He's going over
to Katie's again.

13:04.250 --> 13:06.250
Once a cheater,
always a cheater.

13:06.250 --> 13:08.290
Maybe Stan is just
hanging out with Greg.

13:08.290 --> 13:10.330
Greg works, Maria.
Unlike you.

13:10.330 --> 13:11.830
But I am working.

13:11.830 --> 13:13.080
Working to make me angry!

13:13.080 --> 13:14.170
Now move!

13:15.170 --> 13:17.210
♪♪

13:17.210 --> 13:18.920
Look at you,
nibbling on those crackers

13:18.920 --> 13:20.210
like a little rat.

13:20.210 --> 13:21.580
Hmm.

13:21.580 --> 13:22.920
♪♪

13:22.920 --> 13:25.420
I'm surprised at how clean
you keep this car.

13:25.420 --> 13:26.500
Thank you.

13:26.500 --> 13:28.540
It's like you have pride in it
or something.

13:28.540 --> 13:29.420
Hmm.

13:29.420 --> 13:32.080
♪♪

13:32.080 --> 13:33.830
[ Gasps ]

13:33.830 --> 13:35.830
Twice in a day, Maria?

13:35.830 --> 13:37.880
I haven't done it
twice in a day with him

13:37.880 --> 13:39.880
since Fathers' Day
fell on his birthday.

13:39.880 --> 13:41.120
Oh, God.

13:41.120 --> 13:43.420
I will not be disrespected
like this.

13:43.420 --> 13:45.210
Two can play
at this game.

13:45.210 --> 13:46.080
They're both
gonna be sorry!

13:46.080 --> 13:47.250
[ Gasps ]

13:47.250 --> 13:49.380
God, look at you.
Maria, you're a mess!

13:49.380 --> 13:50.420
Come on, now.

13:50.420 --> 13:52.210
Also, you need a bra
with more support.

13:52.210 --> 13:54.250
I think we need
an HR department.

13:54.250 --> 13:55.710
I think you need
a boob job.

13:59.580 --> 14:02.500
♪♪

14:02.500 --> 14:03.670
[ Bells jingle ]

14:03.670 --> 14:05.420
Hello, Greg.

14:05.420 --> 14:06.960
I came as soon as I got
your message. Where's Stan?

14:06.960 --> 14:08.380
What about Stan?

14:08.380 --> 14:10.080
Well, you said he tripped
and hit his head.

14:10.080 --> 14:11.670
[ Chuckles ]
I made that up.

14:11.670 --> 14:13.250
I don't care about Stan.

14:13.250 --> 14:14.120
I care about you.

14:15.210 --> 14:16.960
The store is closed...

14:16.960 --> 14:18.830
but I'm wide open.

14:18.830 --> 14:20.290
Uh...

14:20.290 --> 14:21.710
Chloe,
what are y-you doing?

14:21.710 --> 14:23.080
Hush, child.
Don't fight it.

14:23.080 --> 14:24.790
Fight what?
Oh, it's okay.

14:24.790 --> 14:26.290
I see the way
you look at me.

14:26.290 --> 14:28.790
It's probably because
my left eye is extra round,

14:28.790 --> 14:30.540
so I have some problems
with depth perception.

14:30.540 --> 14:33.790
Mmm. Tell me more about
your physical defects.

14:33.790 --> 14:35.040
Chloe, stop.
Oh!

14:35.040 --> 14:36.710
Turn the camera off,
Maria!

14:36.710 --> 14:37.920
[ Camera beeps ]
That's a cut.

14:37.920 --> 14:39.710
What's this...
all about?

14:39.710 --> 14:41.330
Revenge,
ya big lug.

14:41.330 --> 14:43.000
Stan and Katie
are doing it.

14:43.000 --> 14:44.290
That's ridiculous.

14:44.290 --> 14:46.210
Oh, really?
Maria, show him.

14:46.210 --> 14:48.380
Look. He's on his way
over there right now.

14:49.960 --> 14:50.960
[ Scoffs ]

14:50.960 --> 14:52.250
There's nothing going on.

14:52.250 --> 14:53.620
Katie's just
feeding him lasagna.

14:53.620 --> 14:55.000
What?!

14:55.000 --> 14:56.420
He's going over there
to eat lasagna?!

14:56.420 --> 14:57.580
Yeah.

14:57.580 --> 14:59.330
Oh,
I'll give him lasagna.

14:59.330 --> 15:01.290
Dirt, coffin floor,
Stan,

15:01.290 --> 15:03.960
coffin lid, dirt,
neglected grave!

15:03.960 --> 15:05.670
O...kay.

15:05.670 --> 15:07.120
♪♪

15:07.120 --> 15:08.920
And after my meeting
with Suzanne,

15:08.920 --> 15:11.040
I realized it's true --

15:11.040 --> 15:12.580
I don't work well
with others.

15:12.580 --> 15:13.540
Mm.

15:13.540 --> 15:15.420
I don't know what to do.

15:15.420 --> 15:17.380
Katie, I'd be more than happy
to set up a consultation for you

15:17.380 --> 15:19.120
with my guru in Nepal.

15:19.120 --> 15:21.710
Sounds like a lot of hiking,
to be honest.

15:21.710 --> 15:22.710
[ Gasps ]

15:22.710 --> 15:24.460
Chloe.
[ Door slams ]

15:24.460 --> 15:27.040
You're eating the lasagna
of my sworn enemy?!

15:27.040 --> 15:28.120
How could you?

15:28.120 --> 15:29.420
He's starving.

15:29.420 --> 15:30.750
How'd you know
I was here?

15:30.750 --> 15:32.960
I was tracking you
on my phone, dummy!

15:32.960 --> 15:35.250
I thought you were
cheating on me again.

15:35.250 --> 15:38.040
Sweetheart, you have
every reason not to trust me.

15:38.040 --> 15:39.500
I messed up.

15:39.500 --> 15:41.210
But I promise
I will never betray you again.

15:42.710 --> 15:43.920
Really?

15:43.920 --> 15:45.420
The one good thing
to come out of all this

15:45.420 --> 15:46.750
is it helped me realize
how much happier I am

15:46.750 --> 15:47.790
with you in my life.

15:47.790 --> 15:49.540
Ohh!

15:49.540 --> 15:52.040
But, honey, I really need
more than 500 calories a day.

15:52.040 --> 15:53.210
Fine.

15:53.210 --> 15:55.420
I'll bump you up
to 800 calories a day.

15:55.420 --> 15:56.620
But no carbs.

15:56.620 --> 15:57.790
Ugh.
Really?

15:57.790 --> 15:58.750
Yes.
I love you.

15:58.750 --> 15:59.790
I love you, too.

15:59.790 --> 16:01.290
Mmm.

16:01.290 --> 16:03.330
This one loves me, too.
She just won't admit it.

16:04.540 --> 16:06.460
The other Katies are talking.
Let's get out of here.

16:10.960 --> 16:13.210
Okay, so, you're not
up for the psychiatric ward.

16:13.210 --> 16:14.580
[ Door opens ]
But how would you feel

16:14.580 --> 16:16.210
about admitting to being
the Zodiac Killer?

16:16.210 --> 16:17.540
[ Door closes ]
No, Oliver!

16:17.540 --> 16:18.960
The dates
don't even line up.

16:18.960 --> 16:20.250
No one's doing the math!

16:21.620 --> 16:23.250
[ Stomping ]

16:23.250 --> 16:24.710
What is wrong
with him?

16:24.710 --> 16:26.580
He's got a big interview later,
but he thinks

16:26.580 --> 16:28.540
he's not going to get in
because he hasn't had

16:28.540 --> 16:31.920
any discrimination or adversity
to overcome.

16:31.920 --> 16:34.460
Well, what about
all of this?

16:34.460 --> 16:36.080
[ Laughs ]

16:36.080 --> 16:37.750
He already made
that same joke.

16:37.750 --> 16:40.290
That selfish dope really needs
to get some perspective.

16:40.290 --> 16:41.670
He doesn't know it,

16:41.670 --> 16:45.040
but this program could be
the best thing for him.

16:45.040 --> 16:46.670
He just needs
to stand out a little.

16:49.330 --> 16:51.250
Why are you looking at us
like that?

16:51.250 --> 16:54.920
Oh. She's picking up
on our sexual tension.

16:54.920 --> 16:56.380
[ Laughs ]
Okay. Okay, Dor.

16:56.380 --> 16:57.710
I -- You know what?

16:57.960 --> 17:00.120
♪♪

17:00.120 --> 17:02.830
Great.
Thank you so much. Bye.

17:02.830 --> 17:05.620
Hi.
I'm Oliver Otto.

17:05.620 --> 17:07.670
I just wanted to say
I'm so excited by the prospect

17:07.670 --> 17:09.790
of being part of
such an important organization.

17:09.790 --> 17:11.000
Hi.
I'm Oliver's Mom.

17:11.000 --> 17:13.120
Hello!
Oliver!

17:13.120 --> 17:14.790
Oh.
Well, one of my moms.

17:14.790 --> 17:16.750
Hi!
Oh!

17:16.750 --> 17:18.080
Very nice to meet you.

17:18.080 --> 17:19.170
Nice to meet you,
too!

17:19.170 --> 17:20.290
Hi.
Hey.

17:21.040 --> 17:22.830
What?
No kiss for your wife?

17:22.830 --> 17:24.670
Oliver, tell your mother
to kiss me.

17:24.670 --> 17:25.670
[ Chuckles ]

17:26.750 --> 17:28.380
[ Clears throat,
chuckles nervously ]

17:31.120 --> 17:32.380
Okay.

17:32.380 --> 17:33.710
See?
Pretty great, right?

17:33.710 --> 17:34.710
Not really.

17:34.710 --> 17:35.920
I'm out of here.
[ Chuckles ]

17:35.920 --> 17:37.120
Bye.

17:37.120 --> 17:39.250
Angela, you know
I can't quit you!

17:40.750 --> 17:42.290
It's from "Brokeback Mountain"
'cause...we're gay.

17:43.460 --> 17:44.580
Hey!!

17:44.580 --> 17:46.580
You are
a terrible wife!

17:46.580 --> 17:48.960
I come from a troubled,
biracial, lesbian home.

17:50.000 --> 17:51.790
But I've developed
emotional tools

17:51.790 --> 17:52.830
to help me deal with it.

17:52.830 --> 17:55.120
♪♪

17:55.120 --> 17:57.040
It was fun
cooking for Stan.

17:57.040 --> 17:58.620
Took my mind off the fact

17:58.620 --> 18:00.880
that I can't find something
to do with my life.

18:00.880 --> 18:02.500
Oh, honey, you can --

18:02.500 --> 18:03.790
Moth!

18:03.790 --> 18:05.120
I got it.
I got it!

18:05.120 --> 18:06.750
Get it!

18:06.750 --> 18:08.120
[ Doorbell rings ]

18:09.540 --> 18:11.120
Oh, hey, Trip.
Hey, Mr. A.

18:11.120 --> 18:12.710
I'm here to pick up Taylor
for the party.

18:12.710 --> 18:14.080
Taylor, Trip's here!

18:18.540 --> 18:20.040
Daisy earrings?

18:20.040 --> 18:21.830
What is the occasion?

18:21.830 --> 18:23.460
Oh, I got my ears pierced
with Anna-Kat

18:23.460 --> 18:24.750
to show her
it was no big deal.

18:24.750 --> 18:26.250
[ Sputtering ]

18:26.250 --> 18:27.920
I'm gonna let the holes
close up,

18:27.920 --> 18:30.120
but I just wanted to feel pretty
for a little while.

18:31.880 --> 18:34.920
What...did you do?

18:34.920 --> 18:36.420
[ Sighs ]

18:38.040 --> 18:39.670
Taylor!
What the hell?!

18:39.670 --> 18:40.920
It's not a big deal!

18:40.920 --> 18:41.920
It is a big deal!

18:41.920 --> 18:43.330
Your job was
to get her new clothes,

18:43.330 --> 18:45.460
not poke holes
in her head!

18:45.460 --> 18:46.710
Trip, Taylor is not
going anywhere tonight.

18:46.710 --> 18:47.620
Wait a second.

18:47.620 --> 18:49.290
You said
to use my best judgment,

18:49.290 --> 18:50.920
and that's exactly
what I did.

18:50.920 --> 18:52.790
Remember when you wouldn't
let me dye my hair blond

18:52.790 --> 18:53.920
but I did it anyway?

18:53.920 --> 18:55.540
Guess what -- not only
did I fit in better,

18:55.540 --> 18:57.000
but it made me
way more confident.

18:57.000 --> 18:58.250
It's not the same!

18:58.250 --> 19:00.080
It's almost exactly
the same!

19:00.080 --> 19:01.380
Now Anna-Kat
has something in common

19:01.380 --> 19:02.880
with all the girls
in her new class!

19:02.880 --> 19:05.420
Plus, I'm not afraid
of needles anymore,

19:05.420 --> 19:07.500
so you don't have to
strap me down at the doctor.

19:10.080 --> 19:12.290
Do you like my earrings?

19:12.290 --> 19:13.670
They're ladybugs.

19:17.460 --> 19:19.170
They're really pretty,
Anna-Kat.

19:20.750 --> 19:24.000
It might not have been
what I would have done,

19:24.000 --> 19:25.500
but you used
your best judgment.

19:27.120 --> 19:29.000
You can cross it
off your list.

19:30.040 --> 19:32.000
So, I can go
to the party?

19:34.120 --> 19:35.210
Have fun.

19:35.210 --> 19:36.580
[ Sighs ]
Thanks, Mom.

19:38.670 --> 19:40.920
Hey, Trip, before you go,
you want to go upstairs

19:40.920 --> 19:43.420
and play "Who wore it best"
with these ladybug earrings?

19:43.420 --> 19:44.960
Oh, yeah.
You're goin' down.
[ Chuckles ]

19:48.750 --> 19:50.460
[ Doorbell rings ]

19:53.000 --> 19:55.420
Hey, Katie. We had a great time
the other night.

19:55.420 --> 19:56.540
Just ask her.

19:56.540 --> 19:57.830
Be cool!

19:57.830 --> 20:00.330
Um, Stan said you might have
some leftover lasagna?

20:00.330 --> 20:02.330
I've honestly never tasted
anything so good.

20:02.330 --> 20:04.040
It was like being back
in my grandmother's kitchen,

20:04.040 --> 20:06.540
except you're not ranting
about how you miss Mussolini.

20:06.540 --> 20:08.960
You guys!
I'm flattered.

20:08.960 --> 20:11.250
Unfortunately,
I'm all out.

20:11.250 --> 20:12.710
Stan had
the last of it today.

20:12.710 --> 20:14.040
We'll pay you
to make another one.

20:14.040 --> 20:14.960
Greg: How much?
30 bucks?

20:14.960 --> 20:16.210
50.
Deal.

20:16.210 --> 20:18.880
Okay. Come back
in three hours.

20:18.880 --> 20:20.170
What do you want to do?

20:20.170 --> 20:21.620
Donuts in
my ex-wife's cul-de-sac?

20:21.620 --> 20:22.790
Fun.
Yeah.

20:24.380 --> 20:26.040
Hang on.

20:26.040 --> 20:28.000
Am I about to get paid
for my lasagna?

20:28.000 --> 20:29.040
It looks like it.

20:29.040 --> 20:30.880
Is this a crazy idea?

20:30.880 --> 20:32.580
Could I make this
a home business?

20:32.580 --> 20:34.290
You absolutely could.
You love cooking.

20:34.290 --> 20:36.080
[ Gasps ]
I'd be my own boss.

20:36.080 --> 20:37.460
I could
make my own hours.

20:37.460 --> 20:39.670
I wouldn't have to manage
or be managed by others.

20:39.670 --> 20:41.330
You could wear pajamas
at work.

20:41.330 --> 20:43.120
That's always been
my dream.

20:43.120 --> 20:44.080
[ Both laugh ]

20:47.960 --> 20:52.040
♪♪

20:52.040 --> 20:53.250
Well, hey.
How'd it go today?

20:53.250 --> 20:54.250
I got accepted.

20:54.250 --> 20:55.460
[ Gasps ]
Oh!

20:55.460 --> 20:57.750
That's great!
That's amazing, honey!

20:58.580 --> 21:00.080
Who knew two diverse --

21:00.080 --> 21:01.210
Ah, ch-ch-ch!

21:01.210 --> 21:02.580
...bickering
lesbian moms --

21:02.580 --> 21:03.830
Ch-ch-ch!

21:03.830 --> 21:04.790
...was my ticket in?

21:06.420 --> 21:08.000
Katie,
what did you do?

21:08.000 --> 21:09.750
[ Smacks lips ]

21:09.750 --> 21:12.420
I did something wrong...

21:12.420 --> 21:14.330
for the right reasons.

21:14.330 --> 21:15.960
Well, I guess
that's an improvement.

21:15.960 --> 21:17.460
Usually, you do the wrong thing
for the wrong reasons.

21:18.880 --> 21:20.580
I'm growing.
Mm.

21:20.580 --> 21:22.460
♪♪

21:25.120 --> 21:29.710
♪♪
